  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6599.91 sitting just below the massive +13.2B gamma wall at 6605, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher into that level while providing buying support at the 6590 negative gamma zone (-5.5B). The PIN regime with 22.5B total GEX creates a strong mean-reversion environment, with the recent wall break and GEX surge indicating heightened dealer hedging activity around these critical strikes. Watch for continued rejection at 6605 and potential bounce dynamics if we test down toward 6590, with the 6623 flip strike acting as the upper bound for bullish continuation.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to get pinned between 6590-6605 with choppy, range-bound action favoring fades of directional moves.",
